<p>27 May 1918<br/>Monday<br/>Still nice fine weather. Paraded for Leave and was granted eight days from Friday next. Going to Scotland. Report the the enemy have commenced another offensive in France.</p>
<p>1918 May 28<br/>Tuesday<br/>Reported Germans have made a substantial advance in the Rheims sector advancing 11 miles Nice fine weather. Same old camp life.</p>
